c({"name": "AD.ListIterator", "type": "class", "comment": "<p>the ListManager object provides an interface to manage a collection (0 or \nmore) of Model instances.  A single ListManager can be shared among several\nwidgets to provide them their data.</p>\n\n<h2>How to use:</h2>\n\n<p>get a ListManager from a Model object:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>       var listViewers = Viewer.listManager({ viewer_isActive:1 });\n             (the provided param object is used as param to findAll();)</code></pre>\n\n<p>pass the ListManager to your widgets:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>       $('#someDiv').appDev_nifty_widget({\n             dataManager:listViewer\n             });</code></pre>\n\n<p>if you want to be alerted when the data in the list changes:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>       listViewers.bind('change', function () {  // do stuff });</code></pre>\n\n<p>To reload the data in the ListManager using bind/trigger</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>     listViewers.refresh();\n     listViewers.findAll({ attrib:value });</code></pre>         (when these complete, listViewers.trigger('change') will fire)\n\n\n To reload the data in the ListManager using deferreds:\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>     var loaded = listViewers.refresh();\n     var loaded = listViewers.findAll({ attrib:value });\n\n     $.when(loaded).done(function () { // do stuff });</code></pre>\n\n<p>These are intended to be use with 1 driver and many listeners.  If <br />\n you have numerous drivers, expect some confusion ...   </p>", "parents": ["AD_Server"], "src": "appDev/data/scripts/appDev/model/listManager.js", "line": 4, "children": ["AD.ListIterator.entryByID"]})